WEBVTT

00:11.479 --> 00:14.348
(choir vocalizing)

00:38.839 --> 00:42.676
- You're going to
pay for my brother.

00:42.710 --> 00:44.078
- I should be the one paying.

00:50.384 --> 00:52.386
- Okay, new plan.

00:52.386 --> 00:54.188
You get Erica, we get Daniel.

00:55.689 --> 00:56.690
- Shit plan.

00:59.059 --> 01:00.328
- Okay.

01:00.328 --> 01:01.329
Fuck everything.

01:01.329 --> 01:04.498
(gun fires)
(man groans)

01:04.532 --> 01:05.533
(knife rasps)

01:05.566 --> 01:07.101
(knife thuds)
(man groans)

01:07.101 --> 01:09.603
(guns firing)

01:21.949 --> 01:22.783
(man groans)

01:22.783 --> 01:24.918
(guns firing)

01:24.918 --> 01:25.753
(man groans)

01:25.753 --> 01:28.256
(guns firing)

01:48.942 --> 01:50.110
- [Erica Voiceover] Shit.

01:51.445 --> 01:52.280
It's my turn.

01:54.315 --> 01:56.450
It's probably only fair.

01:56.450 --> 01:59.287
Considering the amount
of death I dish out,

01:59.287 --> 02:00.588
he was bound to come my way.

02:02.656 --> 02:04.758
Don't let my peaceful
expression fool you.

02:05.959 --> 02:07.795
I'm quite unhappy,
and hurt like hell.

02:10.931 --> 02:11.999
How did we get here?

02:13.301 --> 02:16.470
Well, it's all Daniel's fault.

02:16.470 --> 02:19.006
(gentle music)

03:01.349 --> 03:03.384
No, that's not Daniel.

03:05.786 --> 03:07.187
And this isn't heaven either.

03:09.189 --> 03:12.393
Here, I'm still full of life.

03:12.393 --> 03:14.795
Well, alive at least.

03:18.666 --> 03:22.703
That's me, in my special place,

03:26.206 --> 03:28.309
with a special kind of guy.

03:31.845 --> 03:33.514
This is my special kind of day.

03:39.152 --> 03:42.323
- Do you think
people can change?

03:42.323 --> 03:43.324
- I'm not that deep.

03:45.025 --> 03:46.927
- You're not
answering my question.

03:46.927 --> 03:48.061
- No.

03:48.061 --> 03:48.896
- No?

03:50.331 --> 03:52.400
- I believe people can make
changes to their lives,

03:53.534 --> 03:56.270
become vegan, religious,
taste in music,

03:56.270 --> 03:57.338
but we are who we are.

03:58.939 --> 04:02.943
Thieves steal, murderers
murder, and pedophiles, well--

04:02.943 --> 04:04.778
(gun clicking)

04:04.845 --> 04:07.180
(gun fires)

04:12.252 --> 04:14.855
(gentle music)

04:19.192 --> 04:21.061
- [Erica Voiceover]
I love crocodiles,

04:22.396 --> 04:24.432
but they give most
people the creeps.

04:25.899 --> 04:28.902
Those dead eyes, they just
stare across the water.

04:30.604 --> 04:31.905
But they're bloody clever.

04:33.206 --> 04:36.777
She catches her prey,
drags it to the bottom,

04:36.777 --> 04:39.780
weighs it down, where
it stays and rots.

04:43.784 --> 04:44.652
I love crocodiles.

04:48.088 --> 04:49.122
Merciless.

04:50.824 --> 04:51.892
Fearless.

04:54.328 --> 04:55.429
Timeless.

05:08.175 --> 05:09.743
- Sir, you're a highly
regarded client.

05:09.777 --> 05:11.244
Really highly regarded.

05:11.244 --> 05:13.246
I just think we needn't
hang up on each other again.

05:13.280 --> 05:15.082
This, it's business.

05:15.082 --> 05:16.517
We're grownups.

05:16.517 --> 05:18.519
We're not kids at some farm
trying to hit each other

05:18.519 --> 05:20.120
with clay sticks or something.

05:21.655 --> 05:22.823
Yeah.

05:22.823 --> 05:24.658
No, Wyngaard's gone.

05:24.658 --> 05:25.493
It's Daniel.

05:25.493 --> 05:26.326
Daniel Niemand?

05:27.327 --> 05:28.862
Yeah, from Accounts.

05:28.862 --> 05:30.998
Yes, sir, the fact
is, let's just,

05:30.998 --> 05:33.367
your account's 1.78
million in the red.

05:37.004 --> 05:39.006
And this call is because,

05:40.441 --> 05:43.210
see, sir, I see your wife and
children are in New Zealand?

05:45.112 --> 05:46.447
Looks fun.

05:46.447 --> 05:48.949
And that you've recently
sold your house?

05:50.851 --> 05:51.685
Congrats.

05:53.186 --> 05:55.022
Which brings me to the question,

05:55.055 --> 05:56.990
it's just really
just a question,

05:57.024 --> 05:59.693
sir, are you going to
settle your account with us,

06:00.561 --> 06:02.029
or are you gonna emigrate?

06:05.833 --> 06:06.667
Sir?

06:09.837 --> 06:10.671
Hm.

06:32.159 --> 06:33.594
(people chattering)

06:33.594 --> 06:35.496
(cellphone chimes)

06:38.499 --> 06:40.534
(cellphone chimes)

06:41.669 --> 06:44.071
(cellphone clicking)

06:48.742 --> 06:51.679
(cellphone chimes)

07:00.420 --> 07:01.221
Hey there.

07:04.257 --> 07:06.927
(girl laughing)

07:15.603 --> 07:18.271
(girl laughing)

07:22.976 --> 07:25.646
(girl laughing)

07:34.421 --> 07:35.723
- Hey, hey, you stop that.

07:37.157 --> 07:37.991
Stop it!

07:37.991 --> 07:39.292
Stop.

07:39.292 --> 07:40.460
Don't spray me, hey, don't.

07:40.494 --> 07:42.429
No, you don't, hey.
(girl laughing)

07:42.462 --> 07:43.797
Don't. Stop.

07:43.797 --> 07:45.733
Naughty child, stop that, stop.

07:45.733 --> 07:47.234
- Excuse me, what the
hell are you doing?

07:47.267 --> 07:48.135
- No, no, nothing.

07:48.135 --> 07:49.469
Leave my kid alone!

07:49.469 --> 07:50.638
- She's throwing--
- You sicko, don't touch her!

07:50.671 --> 07:51.905
I'll call the cops!
- Okay, I'll go.

07:51.939 --> 07:54.141
- [Woman] I'll call
the police, watch me.

07:54.141 --> 07:55.308
Just get away.

07:57.978 --> 07:59.813
(Pauline gasps)
(Daniel yelps)

07:59.813 --> 08:00.614
- Hey, babe.

08:02.983 --> 08:04.785
- What the fuck
happened to your suit?

08:04.785 --> 08:06.620
- A little girl threw
a doughnut at me.

08:06.654 --> 08:07.788
- What did you do?

08:07.788 --> 08:08.689
- Nothing.

08:08.689 --> 08:09.857
I just gave her a doughnut.

08:09.857 --> 08:11.625
- Why would you do that?

08:11.659 --> 08:13.527
- I was just sitting there,

08:13.527 --> 08:15.863
then she liked my doughnut,
so I thought I'd be nice

08:15.929 --> 08:17.965
and, you know, give her
the doughnut, you know.

08:17.998 --> 08:19.600
- Bloody hell, what happened?

08:19.600 --> 08:21.535
- Apparently, the girl
he was with did that.

08:21.535 --> 08:23.036
- I wasn't "with" a girl.

08:23.036 --> 08:24.337
- [Pauline] Whatever, Daniel.

08:24.337 --> 08:26.173
- Come in, no one cares.
- But, babe.

08:26.206 --> 08:27.440
Babe.
- Thank you so much.

08:27.474 --> 08:28.642
- It'll be one of the--
- Excuse me, Reverend.

08:28.642 --> 08:30.110
- Sure, sure.
- It'll be amazing.

08:30.110 --> 08:31.679
Cousin Daniel.

08:31.679 --> 08:32.946
- [Daniel] Cousin Daniel.

08:33.847 --> 08:35.215
- I'm so glad you could make it.

08:35.215 --> 08:36.216
Thank you.
- Sorry.

08:37.517 --> 08:38.852
Why is Schalk here?

08:38.852 --> 08:40.688
- You got my email about
the dress code, right?

08:40.688 --> 08:42.189
- Yeah.

08:42.189 --> 08:44.357
- Magriet will squeeze my
balls blue if I forget.

08:44.357 --> 08:45.225
(Daniel chuckles)

08:45.292 --> 08:47.360
- I can imagine.
- Daniel?

08:47.360 --> 08:48.796
- Babe.
- Oh.

08:48.829 --> 08:50.998
Oh, it's the other
Cousin Daniel.

08:50.998 --> 08:52.399
Oh.

08:52.399 --> 08:53.667
For a moment there, I
thought your friendly cousin

08:53.701 --> 08:55.002
had brought home a hobo again.

08:55.002 --> 08:55.836
(Magriet chuckles)

08:55.836 --> 08:56.837
- They're people too.

08:58.371 --> 09:00.140
- You're probably
putting something else on

09:00.173 --> 09:01.341
for the photos, right?

09:01.341 --> 09:02.342
- Don't worry
about him, Magriet.

09:02.375 --> 09:03.376
He'll look perfect.

09:03.376 --> 09:04.344
Come.
- Excuse me.

09:05.713 --> 09:07.514
- There's a bit on your nose.

09:10.050 --> 09:11.652
Oh, come on,

09:11.652 --> 09:12.853
it's totally fine.
- It's your family.

09:12.886 --> 09:14.588
- It's fine, they'll
clean him up.

09:14.588 --> 09:16.389
- Ugh.
- It's fine.

09:16.389 --> 09:18.558
It's fine, babes,
just breathe, babes.

09:24.564 --> 09:26.399
- I thought your dad
walking out on us

09:26.433 --> 09:27.935
would be the biggest disgrace.

09:27.935 --> 09:29.837
- Mom, it really
wasn't my fault.

09:29.870 --> 09:31.772
- Why do you keep
doing this to me?

09:31.772 --> 09:32.706
- Doing what?

09:32.740 --> 09:34.107
- [Jozette] Ugh, what a mess.

09:34.107 --> 09:36.276
- This was one of
Daniel's old ones.

09:36.276 --> 09:37.277
It might fit.

09:37.277 --> 09:38.846
- That was the best I could do.

09:41.381 --> 09:42.215
Mm.

09:45.452 --> 09:48.121
- I wanted to do this
sooner, but you were late.

09:48.121 --> 09:49.556
- I'm not having a great day.

09:49.589 --> 09:50.958
- Schalk and I are together.

09:54.394 --> 09:55.629
- Schalk?

09:55.629 --> 09:57.765
Our marriage counselor Schalk?

09:57.765 --> 09:58.598
- Yes.

10:01.434 --> 10:02.269
- Since when?

10:05.072 --> 10:08.241
- I would say somewhere
around the third session.

10:08.275 --> 10:09.943
One of our individual sessions.

10:09.943 --> 10:12.079
It was one thing
and then another.

10:12.112 --> 10:13.914
You know how these
things happen.

10:13.914 --> 10:14.748
- Have you two...

10:16.483 --> 10:17.651
- It doesn't really matter.

10:17.718 --> 10:18.986
- Doesn't matter?

10:18.986 --> 10:20.320
- No, I wanna chat
about something else.

10:20.320 --> 10:21.789
- Chat?

10:21.789 --> 10:23.423
- It's Schalk's
professional opinion

10:23.456 --> 10:27.060
that if I wanna be healed,
we should get divorced.

10:32.432 --> 10:35.002
He says he's seen this
happen to lots of couples.

10:38.672 --> 10:40.407
- Maybe we should
just connect a bit.

10:40.440 --> 10:41.274
Come here, just--
- Mm-mm.

10:41.274 --> 10:42.642
- Just come here.

10:45.612 --> 10:46.680
Is this about the money?

10:46.680 --> 10:47.915
'Cause if it's about the money--

10:47.948 --> 10:49.449
- Daniel, please,
just sign the papers.

10:50.684 --> 10:52.085
I won't ask for anything.

10:53.120 --> 10:54.154
I just want the house.

10:55.322 --> 10:56.123
And the money.

10:58.325 --> 11:01.762
But all your things are at
your apartment, anyway, right?

11:01.762 --> 11:03.530
Things are actually
working out wonderfully,

11:03.530 --> 11:04.597
don't you think?

11:04.631 --> 11:05.866
Go on, Daniel, take this off.

11:05.866 --> 11:06.867
God, it stinks.

11:08.535 --> 11:11.271
(girl squealing)

11:17.144 --> 11:18.145
- [Man] Taking these photos--

11:18.145 --> 11:18.979
- Mom?
- Before the wedding's

11:18.979 --> 11:19.880
a great idea.

11:19.880 --> 11:21.281
- Cousin Daniel has always been

11:21.314 --> 11:22.182
forward thinking.
- We have to talk.

11:22.182 --> 11:23.016
- Oh.
- Thank you.

11:23.016 --> 11:23.851
- Yes, pardon me.

11:25.352 --> 11:26.519
- So she gave it to you.

11:28.521 --> 11:29.723
- Mom?

11:29.790 --> 11:31.324
- You're holding
her back, Daniel.

11:31.358 --> 11:32.192
- Back from what?

11:32.192 --> 11:33.827
- She's outgrown you.

11:33.861 --> 11:37.497
I mean, you're without
any ambition, and
lately, so passive.

11:37.497 --> 11:39.900
It must have been
very frustrating for
her, I can imagine.

11:39.900 --> 11:40.734
- Hi.

11:42.202 --> 11:44.738
- I'm sorry, son, but everyone
thinks it's for the best.

11:45.705 --> 11:47.374
- Who's "everyone"?

11:47.407 --> 11:49.743
- It's all my fault, Pauline.
- Mom.

11:49.810 --> 11:51.244
Mom?

11:51.244 --> 11:53.213
- I should've known after
30 hours in labor...

11:54.347 --> 11:55.849
Just like his dad.

11:55.883 --> 11:57.550
Imagine what could've been
if I'd rather introduced you

11:57.550 --> 11:58.651
to our dear Cousin Daniel.

11:58.685 --> 12:00.220
- Oh, don't worry, Mom.

12:00.220 --> 12:02.355
I really loved your
Daniel very much,

12:02.389 --> 12:03.991
once upon a time.
- We all did.

12:05.225 --> 12:07.260
At least, now, you have Schalk.

12:07.327 --> 12:08.495
- [Pauline] Oh, yes.

12:08.528 --> 12:09.562
- [Schalk] Hey, Daniel.

12:09.562 --> 12:10.530
- Hey, Schalk.

12:10.563 --> 12:11.431
Schalk.
- Hm?

12:14.001 --> 12:16.003
Okay, look at me.

12:17.838 --> 12:19.272
Everything will be okay.

12:19.272 --> 12:20.440
I promise.

12:20.507 --> 12:21.508
Okay?

12:21.508 --> 12:22.509
This is for the best.

12:22.509 --> 12:23.343
Come here.

12:23.343 --> 12:24.177
Just like we practiced.

12:24.177 --> 12:25.245
In deep.

12:25.245 --> 12:26.079
That's it.

12:27.848 --> 12:29.883
And out, okay, cool.

12:29.917 --> 12:30.918
Chat with you later.

12:32.085 --> 12:34.221
- Chat?
- All right, is everyone here?

12:34.221 --> 12:37.724
All right, can the
family please step up?

12:38.591 --> 12:40.227
Bride and groom in the middle.

12:40.260 --> 12:41.528
- See you soon, all right?
- See you soon.

12:41.528 --> 12:42.729
- [Photographer] Uh-huh,
all right, that's good.

12:42.762 --> 12:44.798
All right, Granny,
Grandpa, over here.

12:46.599 --> 12:49.469
Yeah, all right, let's get all
the children to squeeze in.

12:51.704 --> 12:53.240
All right, yeah, it's
starting to look nice.

12:53.273 --> 12:54.074
- Cuz.
- Hm?

12:55.308 --> 12:57.144
- He's not in the color scheme.

12:57.144 --> 12:58.111
- He's my cousin.

12:58.111 --> 12:59.712
- What about the color scheme?

12:59.746 --> 13:00.914
- Schalk is in the color scheme.

13:00.914 --> 13:02.049
- What?
- Come on.

13:02.049 --> 13:03.116
- Oh, Schalk.
- No, no, no, I can't.

13:03.116 --> 13:04.217
- Come on.
- It's not my place.

13:04.251 --> 13:05.152
If you insist.

13:06.753 --> 13:07.587
I love photos!

13:09.122 --> 13:10.223
- [Magriet] Oh, perfect.

13:13.726 --> 13:15.562
- [Schalk] Oh, this
just feels right.

13:16.796 --> 13:18.565
- [Photographer] Oh,
yeah, this looks good.

13:19.933 --> 13:21.234
Excuse me. You.

13:21.234 --> 13:22.435
- Yeah?
- What's your name?

13:22.469 --> 13:23.803
- Daniel.
- Would you mind

13:23.803 --> 13:25.138
holding the ladder, please?

13:26.806 --> 13:28.008
- No, no, all right.

13:28.008 --> 13:29.642
- [Photographer] Oh,
thank you, Daniel.

13:31.811 --> 13:33.313
All right, (grunts) here we go.

13:34.781 --> 13:37.450
All right, okay,
I'll count to three,

13:37.450 --> 13:39.519
then all of you say "family!"

13:39.519 --> 13:41.521
One, two, three.
- Family!

13:41.588 --> 13:43.423
(camera snaps)

13:43.423 --> 13:44.491
- [Photographer]
One, two, three.

13:44.491 --> 13:45.859
Family!
- Family!

13:46.826 --> 13:49.963
- Family!
(man laughs)

13:49.963 --> 13:52.132
(horn honks)

13:52.132 --> 13:54.001
(policeman whistles)

13:54.001 --> 13:56.336
- [Policeman]
Let's go, let's go!

13:56.369 --> 13:59.339
Let's go, let's go, let's go!

13:59.339 --> 14:02.542
(policeman whistling)

14:02.609 --> 14:05.278
(siren wailing)

14:07.047 --> 14:09.449
(people chattering)

14:09.482 --> 14:12.986
(police radio chattering)

14:13.853 --> 14:17.024
(helicopter whirring)

14:26.366 --> 14:28.335
- [Erica Voiceover]
I love dark humor,

14:28.368 --> 14:31.905
but a chopped up body in a shape
of a smiley face on a beach

14:31.905 --> 14:34.174
is a bit much, even for me.

14:35.675 --> 14:39.012
When you're a civil servant,
a sense of humor is crucial,

14:40.547 --> 14:43.383
but this is a big middle finger
for a grumpy, old bugger.

14:47.354 --> 14:49.256
Detective Johannes Ackerman.

14:52.859 --> 14:54.594
- Has the body been
identified yet?

14:56.829 --> 14:59.832
- Yes, a certain
Petrus Wyngaard.

15:01.068 --> 15:02.402
Or, at least, bits of him.

15:03.770 --> 15:05.238
- Mm.

15:05.238 --> 15:07.574
Well, whoever did this
has a sick sense of humor.

15:09.542 --> 15:12.612
- Apparently, one of Frank's
previous accountants.

15:12.612 --> 15:14.614
(dog barking)

15:14.681 --> 15:16.849
- [Woman] Oh, jeez, get
your dog under control!

15:16.849 --> 15:17.951
- [Frank] Hey, fuck off!

15:17.951 --> 15:19.619
- Speak of the devil.

15:19.686 --> 15:21.454
Frank Redelinghuys.

15:21.454 --> 15:25.792
(choir singing in
foreign language)

15:47.447 --> 15:49.983
Are you the latest oil
tanker to crash the beach?

15:50.050 --> 15:51.784
What are you doing here, Frank?

15:51.784 --> 15:54.421
- How are retirement
plans coming along?

15:54.454 --> 15:55.722
I suggest you take it easy,

15:55.722 --> 15:58.125
you know, for the
last few weeks.

15:58.125 --> 15:59.892
One wouldn't want
to break a hip, huh?

15:59.926 --> 16:01.894
(men laughing)

16:01.894 --> 16:03.230
I hope the minister of police

16:03.230 --> 16:06.399
will at least wash your
feet the day you leave.

16:06.399 --> 16:08.601
- You want one of my
feet up your ass, Frank?

16:10.803 --> 16:12.339
- If you worked for me.

16:12.339 --> 16:14.507
I like to thank my
employees personally

16:14.507 --> 16:16.343
on the day they
leave my service.

16:17.677 --> 16:20.747
- People appreciate the
personal touch, Frank.

16:20.780 --> 16:22.449
- Yes, that's true, isn't it?

16:22.449 --> 16:25.185
- Mm-hm.
- Yes, I think so too.

16:25.185 --> 16:26.186
- [Policeman] Captain.

16:27.654 --> 16:30.790
- [Frank] A little something
for your selfless service.

16:32.625 --> 16:33.760
- [Xander] What's that?

16:34.761 --> 16:36.363
- A warrant.

16:36.363 --> 16:37.930
- That's the first
one you gave me.

16:37.964 --> 16:41.434
I kept it for 20 long years.

16:41.434 --> 16:43.970
I thought you might
want to frame it.

16:44.003 --> 16:45.672
Enjoy your day, Captain.

16:46.639 --> 16:47.807
Always a pleasure.

16:49.209 --> 16:50.043
Come.

16:52.945 --> 16:53.880
- [Johannes] Shit!

16:53.880 --> 16:55.115
- Captain!
- What?

16:55.148 --> 16:57.184
- [Xander] The scene
can't be, you know...

16:59.952 --> 17:02.889
- Ever since I put
this on 35 years ago,

17:02.889 --> 17:05.392
I haven't broken a single
municipal regulation.

17:05.458 --> 17:07.560
And you know what the
hell that got me?!

17:07.560 --> 17:08.661
Fuck all!

17:08.695 --> 17:10.029
It got me fuck all!

17:14.534 --> 17:17.137
(gentle music)

17:38.358 --> 17:43.363
(blinds clacking)
(knocking)

17:55.908 --> 17:56.743
- Daniel.

17:58.411 --> 17:59.279
Look at me.

18:00.347 --> 18:01.114
Hey!

18:03.049 --> 18:03.883
Hm?

18:05.852 --> 18:07.420
How long have you worked for me?

18:10.790 --> 18:12.592
