37:12.230 --> 37:14.666
You have the right
to remain silent.

37:14.700 --> 37:16.768
You have the right
to remain silent.

37:16.768 --> 37:19.438
Anything you say
can and will be used

37:19.505 --> 37:21.740
against you in a court of law.

37:21.740 --> 37:23.842
You have the right
to talk to a lawyer,

37:23.875 --> 37:25.877
and have them present.

37:25.877 --> 37:26.712
- Cheers, gentlemen.

37:26.712 --> 37:27.946
Enjoy your day.

37:27.946 --> 37:30.616
Seems you jumped the gun
with your farewell gift.

37:30.616 --> 37:32.017
See you at the party, Frank.

37:47.933 --> 37:50.636
- Don't you all
have work to do?!

37:52.471 --> 37:54.239
- [Policeman] Please,
don't smile, sir.

37:55.106 --> 37:56.141
(camera snaps)
Next!

37:57.643 --> 37:59.745
- What does Z stand for?
- Sir, I'm not gonna

37:59.778 --> 38:00.812
ask you again.
- Hey.

38:02.448 --> 38:03.582
- [Man In Hat] Is it Zoe?

38:03.582 --> 38:04.650
- Hey, hey, hey!
- I said leave me alone!

38:04.650 --> 38:07.152
(officers shouting)

38:07.218 --> 38:09.588
- [Man In Hat]
Hey, fuck you, man.

38:09.621 --> 38:10.822
I'm watching you!

38:10.822 --> 38:12.057
(Xander speaking in
foreign language)

38:12.090 --> 38:14.326
I'll dream about
you tonight, baby!

38:14.326 --> 38:15.794
- [Xander] Put
him in cell three!

38:15.794 --> 38:17.162
- [Man In Hat] I love you!

38:17.228 --> 38:18.897
(stapler clacks)

38:18.930 --> 38:19.831
- [Xander] All right,
give me that file.

38:19.831 --> 38:20.666
Come on.

38:25.103 --> 38:26.905
- [Daniel] Can I
use the bathroom?

38:26.905 --> 38:28.407
- [Xander] No, there's no time.

38:28.440 --> 38:29.341
- [Policeman] Next.

38:33.479 --> 38:35.447
- [Hansie] Why are
you so fucking calm?

38:36.948 --> 38:39.451
- Well, hopefully, Daniel
will bark the right tune.

38:39.451 --> 38:42.954
In which case, we'll
make his time in jail

38:42.988 --> 38:44.590
as pleasant as possible.

38:45.991 --> 38:48.093
- [Hansie] Or he's a little
tattletale and spills the beans.

38:48.093 --> 38:50.295
- Then I'll have something
to feed to my dog.

38:52.531 --> 38:53.865
Is that scene clean?

38:55.333 --> 38:56.267
- [Hansie] Of course that
scene's clean, Frank.

38:56.267 --> 38:57.769
This isn't my first rodeo.

38:57.803 --> 38:58.804
- It's bothering me.

39:02.508 --> 39:04.676
So how does Acker know?

39:07.846 --> 39:09.515
- Ooh, I want your healing.
- Just want my healing?

39:09.548 --> 39:11.950
- [Pauline] Heal me, God,
do what you have to do.

39:11.983 --> 39:15.053
I deeply need it.
- I'll give you some healing.

39:15.053 --> 39:16.221
(Pauline moans)

39:16.287 --> 39:17.322
- [Pauline] Oh, God, oh,

39:17.355 --> 39:18.524
give it to me, baby.
- Okay.

39:18.524 --> 39:19.825
- No, no, keep watching.

39:19.858 --> 39:21.560
- [Schalk] You know what
I mean when I say deep?

39:21.560 --> 39:23.361
- [Pauline] Give it to me.

39:23.361 --> 39:24.996
(Schalk moans)
Oh, I'm with you.

39:25.030 --> 39:26.231
- [Schalk] That
deep enough for you?

39:26.231 --> 39:27.399
- [Pauline] Oh, God, yeah, yeah

39:27.399 --> 39:28.333
- Yeah?
- Yeah, yeah.

39:28.366 --> 39:29.801
- Why are you showing me this?

39:29.801 --> 39:31.236
- Deep.
(Pauline moaning)

39:31.236 --> 39:32.738
- How could you not
know about the camera?

39:32.804 --> 39:34.540
It's not like he
tried to hide it.

39:34.540 --> 39:36.007
- [Schalk] Do you feel that?

39:36.041 --> 39:38.877
- Yeah, your wife's a star,
in quite a few of these.

39:38.877 --> 39:40.846
Believe me, she's a star.

39:40.846 --> 39:42.347
- My ex-wife.

39:42.347 --> 39:43.181
- Ex-wife?

39:44.315 --> 39:45.884
According to her,
she was ready to make

39:45.884 --> 39:47.586
the gem's sequel last night.

39:47.653 --> 39:49.555
- Only, when she got
to Schalk's house--

39:49.555 --> 39:51.056
- There was no Schalk.

39:51.056 --> 39:52.390
- But there was this video.

39:53.592 --> 39:54.860
- [Schalk] Daniel, hit me

39:54.893 --> 39:56.394
right here, okay?
- I am in control.

39:56.394 --> 39:57.663
- Okay, you're in control.
- I am in control.

39:57.696 --> 39:58.930
You won't get me down!

39:58.930 --> 39:59.831
(Schalk groans)

39:59.865 --> 40:02.701
(Schalk coughing)

40:04.402 --> 40:06.572
- Seriously, though, didn't
you realize there was a camera?

40:06.572 --> 40:07.706
- He told me to hit him.

40:07.739 --> 40:09.441
Schalk told me to hit him.

40:09.441 --> 40:10.942
- [Johannes] We heard that.

40:10.942 --> 40:13.011
- "You won't get me down,
you won't get me down."

40:13.044 --> 40:15.046
- But what we didn't
hear was him asking you

40:15.080 --> 40:16.882
to cut a hole in his throat.

40:16.882 --> 40:18.584
- I saved his life, okay?

40:18.584 --> 40:19.685
He wasn't dead.

40:19.718 --> 40:21.887
- Then what happened,
Mr. Niemand?

40:21.887 --> 40:24.222
- I accidentally hit him
in the throat, so I did

40:24.222 --> 40:26.625
an emergency tracheotomy.
- An emergency tracheotomy?

40:26.625 --> 40:28.794
- Dr. McDreamy, where'd
you learn that shit?

40:29.861 --> 40:31.697
- Scouts, okay?

40:31.730 --> 40:33.231
I saved his life.

40:33.264 --> 40:34.900
- And then you took
him to hospital,

40:34.900 --> 40:37.969
except there's no Schalk
Bosch in any hospital.

40:37.969 --> 40:41.239
See, we followed up
on this, Mr. Niemand.

40:41.272 --> 40:42.474
Where's Schalk?

40:42.474 --> 40:43.441
- [Xander] He's dead,
isn't he, Daniel?

40:43.441 --> 40:45.644
- [Johannes] Where's his body?

40:45.711 --> 40:46.545
- I can't say.

40:50.882 --> 40:52.551
(Johannes sighs)

40:52.551 --> 40:55.053
- How long have you been
working for Frank Redelinghuys?

40:59.124 --> 41:01.259
- Two years, three months.

41:01.259 --> 41:02.994
- You must've seen
plenty in that time.

41:02.994 --> 41:04.162
- Plenty.

41:04.229 --> 41:05.897
- I work in Excel a lot.

41:05.931 --> 41:08.266
I didn't see anything.

41:08.299 --> 41:09.568
- Mm-hm.

41:09.568 --> 41:12.003
Mr. Niemand, I think
this is what happened:

41:12.003 --> 41:14.806
You didn't mean to kill
Schalk Bosch, I understand.

41:14.806 --> 41:16.908
But this guy fucked your wife.

41:18.109 --> 41:19.778
I know I would've
lost my temper,

41:19.778 --> 41:22.247
but when things started
cooling off, you had a problem.

41:22.247 --> 41:25.751
- An emergency trache, tricheo--

41:25.784 --> 41:27.285
- Tracheotomy.

41:27.318 --> 41:29.154
- Tri, trichemy.

41:29.154 --> 41:30.155
Yeah, all right.

41:32.490 --> 41:35.694
There must've been lots of
blood, and then the body,

41:35.761 --> 41:39.264
not things that tend
to clean themselves.

41:39.297 --> 41:41.299
- And, Louw, who
would you have called

41:41.332 --> 41:42.968
to help you get rid of the body?

41:42.968 --> 41:43.769
- Hmm.

41:44.670 --> 41:46.171
It's hard to say, Captain.

41:46.171 --> 41:50.208
I don't really hang out with
people like that, but, mm,

41:51.610 --> 41:53.945
but if Frank Redelinghuys
was my boss--

41:53.979 --> 41:56.715
- Mm-hm, Louw, I
think you're right.

41:56.715 --> 41:58.650
That's what I would've
done, Mr. Niemand.

41:58.684 --> 41:59.651
- It's not what happened.

41:59.651 --> 42:00.719
- Then what happened?!

42:00.719 --> 42:01.519
- Speak!
- What happened?!

42:01.519 --> 42:02.621
- I can't tell you.

42:02.654 --> 42:03.722
They'll kill me, okay?

42:03.722 --> 42:04.890
- Who will kill you?

42:04.890 --> 42:06.391
- I can't tell you.

42:06.457 --> 42:08.660
(knocking)
- What?!

42:08.694 --> 42:09.695
- [Policeman] Captain?

42:12.063 --> 42:14.399
(Johannes grunts)

42:14.399 --> 42:16.635
- [Xander] Come on, move it.

42:16.668 --> 42:18.469
- [Johannes] You're joking.

42:18.469 --> 42:20.238
- I don't have sense of humor.

42:20.238 --> 42:23.675
There isn't a single print or
pube anywhere in the house.

42:23.709 --> 42:24.910
(Johannes groans)

42:24.910 --> 42:27.312
Nothing Schalk Bosch
can be identified by.

42:27.345 --> 42:29.881
- So it's been
professionally cleaned.

42:29.881 --> 42:31.016
Again.

42:31.049 --> 42:32.217
- Yeah, absolutely.

42:32.217 --> 42:34.219
I would say if it
wasn't for the video,

42:34.252 --> 42:37.255
there would've been, like, no
way to say who or what did it.

42:38.890 --> 42:40.058
I'm sorry, Hannes.

42:40.058 --> 42:41.392
- [Johannes] No, it's okay.

42:52.570 --> 42:53.839
- Surely, you don't
think that miserable

42:53.839 --> 42:54.940
son of a bitch did it.

42:56.708 --> 42:58.209
He can't go to prison,

42:58.209 --> 43:00.946
they'll hand him around like
a package of Jelly Tots.

43:00.946 --> 43:03.381
- No, this is Frank
and Hansie's work.

43:03.414 --> 43:05.416
- And you know his
testimony isn't enough

43:05.416 --> 43:06.685
for a conviction, right?

43:06.685 --> 43:08.253
If he goes to court, even.

43:08.253 --> 43:10.689
- Frank's legal team
will eat him alive.

43:10.722 --> 43:12.557
- That's if Frank lets
him into the court

43:12.590 --> 43:14.626
in anything other
than a body bag.

43:14.626 --> 43:15.460
- [Johannes] Mm.

43:16.928 --> 43:17.763
Right.

43:21.700 --> 43:23.201
- And now?

43:23.201 --> 43:25.603
- Frank's strong point has
always been our weak point.

43:25.603 --> 43:29.574
The slippery bastard
is unpredictable,
except for one thing:

43:31.743 --> 43:35.947
His informants have a tendency
to disappear, or worse.

43:35.947 --> 43:37.949
- So what do you suggest?

43:37.949 --> 43:39.885
- Well, for now, we
have his witness.

43:39.918 --> 43:42.587
I suggest we put
him somewhere safe,

43:42.620 --> 43:46.124
and in the meantime, we're
gonna keep an eye on Frank.

43:46.124 --> 43:47.893
When Frank catches
up with this guy

43:47.926 --> 43:49.494
and does his thing, we got him.

43:50.829 --> 43:53.064
- Surely, you mean
before he does his thing.

43:55.000 --> 43:56.634
You want this poor idiot killed?

44:02.640 --> 44:04.810
- Life gives each of
us a handful of cards.

44:06.244 --> 44:10.481
How we play, well, that's
up to us, but play we must.

44:11.482 --> 44:12.483
- My cards are shit.

44:12.483 --> 44:14.953
- Yeah, they are.

44:14.986 --> 44:18.356
But what if I could
deal you a new hand, hm?

44:19.490 --> 44:20.291
Hm?

44:21.459 --> 44:22.961
Do you know anything
about WITSEC?

44:22.994 --> 44:24.095
- Witness Protection.

44:25.363 --> 44:26.765
- We could hide you away.

44:26.798 --> 44:28.934
Give you a new
identity, a new life.

44:30.035 --> 44:31.536
- I'm in.

44:31.602 --> 44:32.771
- Give me something I can use,

44:32.804 --> 44:34.672
and we'll send you
off to your new life.

44:35.807 --> 44:39.177
And Frank Redelinghuys
to his new one.

44:39.177 --> 44:40.345
Jail.

44:40.345 --> 44:41.479
- Sounds good.

44:41.512 --> 44:43.681
- Our program's one of the best.

44:43.681 --> 44:46.184
And Lieutenant Kruger
is the best of the best.

44:46.184 --> 44:48.887
- If Lieutenant Kruger hides
you, no one will find you.

44:50.355 --> 44:52.523
- I don't know if you
heard, but I said I'm in.

44:53.691 --> 44:55.226
Let's go?

44:55.226 --> 44:56.061
Please?

44:57.195 --> 44:58.129
- Tea or coffee?

44:59.197 --> 45:00.065
- Just some water.

45:02.567 --> 45:04.402
And then I was back at work

45:04.402 --> 45:06.404
and everything was
back to normal.

45:08.639 --> 45:09.507
And that's it.

45:12.677 --> 45:15.747
- Everything will work out,
Mr. Niemand, you'll see.

45:15.747 --> 45:16.915
(knocking)
Yes?

45:18.750 --> 45:20.385
- Lieutenant Kruger's here.

45:20.385 --> 45:21.686
- [Johannes] Okay, thanks.

45:23.154 --> 45:25.690
(gentle music)

45:30.395 --> 45:32.397
Lieutenant Kruger,
I'm glad you made it.

45:33.231 --> 45:34.732
- Louw said it's urgent.

45:34.732 --> 45:36.234
- Extremely.

45:36.267 --> 45:38.103
The man in there is Frank
Redelinghuys's accountant.

45:38.103 --> 45:39.905
He refuses to testify in court,

45:39.905 --> 45:41.940
but we have a recording of it.

45:42.007 --> 45:44.375
And I suspect, as soon
as Frank finds out,

45:44.409 --> 45:45.743
the shit hits the fan.

45:45.743 --> 45:47.712
There's enough to send
him to prison for life.

45:47.712 --> 45:49.380
- So he has to disappear?

45:49.414 --> 45:51.416
- [Johannes]
Exactly, right away.

45:51.416 --> 45:53.751
According to him, Frank's
already threatened his life.

45:53.751 --> 45:55.253
Plus, witness protection...

45:56.587 --> 45:58.523
- [Erica Voiceover]
Look for the devil,

45:58.556 --> 46:00.358
and you will find him.

46:00.358 --> 46:03.428
Too many pedophiles, they
all start looking the same.

46:03.428 --> 46:04.529
Shame.

46:04.562 --> 46:05.730
- [Johannes] So, when...

46:08.099 --> 46:10.768
- [Erica Voiceover]
Shame for both of us.

46:10.768 --> 46:12.203
- I'm Lieutenant Kruger.

46:12.237 --> 46:15.240
If you want to live, do
exactly as I say, understood?

46:15.240 --> 46:16.541
- Yep.

46:16.541 --> 46:18.409
- Anything else from your side?

46:18.443 --> 46:20.245
- Are you leaving already?

46:20.245 --> 46:21.913
- This is what will happen next:

46:21.947 --> 46:24.482
When I walk out the door,
you will wait 10 minutes,

46:24.482 --> 46:27.152
then you move to the lowest
level of the parking area.

46:27.218 --> 46:28.253
Wait for me there.

46:33.291 --> 46:35.126
- Am I going with her?

46:36.394 --> 46:37.562
- [Johannes] Daniel,
for the record,

46:37.595 --> 46:39.264
can you please
use his full name?

46:40.932 --> 46:43.168
- [Daniel] Frank Redelinghuys.

46:43.168 --> 46:46.237
Frank Redelinghuys shot
Schalk Bosch in the head.

46:46.271 --> 46:47.772
- See, I've watched
you and Acker

46:47.805 --> 46:49.640
dance with each other for
years now, it's beautiful.

46:49.640 --> 46:53.478
He catches you, and you
slip through his fingers.

46:53.478 --> 46:55.313
- [Frank] Blood is slippery.

46:55.313 --> 46:56.581
- So I've heard.

46:56.614 --> 46:58.116
My point is, Frank,
I don't like losing.

46:59.417 --> 47:01.152
I'm fed up with it.

47:01.152 --> 47:03.621
- You want to play
for the other team?

47:03.654 --> 47:06.858
- I wouldn't put it quite
like that, but yeah.

47:06.858 --> 47:09.861
- By giving me the recording?

47:11.262 --> 47:13.932
- [Xander] Uh-huh, by
giving you something better.

47:13.965 --> 47:16.267
(cellphone beeps)

47:16.267 --> 47:17.335
- [Frank] What's that?

47:18.970 --> 47:20.638
- [Xander] This
is Daniel Niemand.

47:24.976 --> 47:26.978
- [Frank] That little dot?

47:27.012 --> 47:28.679
- He's at your police station.

47:28.679 --> 47:29.981
- At the moment, yeah.

47:31.449 --> 47:33.885
But in a few minutes, even
I won't know his location.

47:33.885 --> 47:36.621
- Are you taking me
for a fool, Inspector?

47:36.654 --> 47:39.457
- Maybe, but this GPS is
the only way to find out.

47:40.858 --> 47:43.294
I suggest you do it
before the battery dies.

47:44.229 --> 47:47.398
I'd say you have
about six hours.

47:51.302 --> 47:52.137
Hmm?

47:54.072 --> 47:56.074
Bon appetit, gentlemen.

47:56.141 --> 47:58.076
I heard the moussaka
is fantastic.

48:01.179 --> 48:03.014
- [Frank] Okay, wait!

48:03.048 --> 48:03.881
- [Hansie] Frank.

48:04.815 --> 48:06.151
- [Frank] What do you want?

48:07.585 --> 48:11.056
- Okay, cellphone, wallet,
any other personal items?

48:14.725 --> 48:18.096
Keep your arms stretched out.
(device beeps)

48:18.096 --> 48:19.030
(device beeps)

48:19.064 --> 48:21.766
(device beeping)

48:33.411 --> 48:36.214
Last chance, get into the
car, and your new life begins.

48:42.387 --> 48:43.721
Lie low and hide your face.

48:48.726 --> 48:51.362
(tires screeching)

48:51.362 --> 48:54.365
(cellphone beeping)

48:59.937 --> 49:02.773
(computer beeping)

49:10.081 --> 49:12.250
- [Xander] Captain,
yeah, he took the bait.

49:14.552 --> 49:16.154
- [Erica Voiceover] To
reach the middle of nowhere,

49:16.154 --> 49:17.488
you have to drive very far.

49:20.258 --> 49:22.760
Past all the
somewheres out there.

49:25.796 --> 49:26.931
But I like nowhere.

49:28.599 --> 49:33.604
(car seat whirring)
(button clicking)

49:57.462 --> 49:58.296
- Wow.

49:59.330 --> 50:00.165
This is pretty.

50:04.835 --> 50:06.337
So what's next?

50:06.337 --> 50:08.439
- See, there's a house in
the mountains I often use.

50:08.473 --> 50:10.041
No one knows about it except me.

50:11.509 --> 50:14.379
We'll wait there until your
new identity's in the system.

50:14.379 --> 50:15.480
Few weeks max.

50:15.513 --> 50:16.347
- Sounds good.

50:18.449 --> 50:19.450
Will I get a new name?

50:19.484 --> 50:20.318
- [Erica] Yes.

50:22.853 --> 50:24.555
- Okay, can it be
something badass?

50:25.790 --> 50:29.860
Something like Jack
Ace, or Tom Black.

50:33.698 --> 50:35.700
- You'll get a name
from our database.

50:35.733 --> 50:38.469
Something commonplace
from your year of birth,

50:38.503 --> 50:42.073
Jan, Johan, Fourie, Van der
Merwe, something like that.

50:42.073 --> 50:42.873
- Okay.

50:44.509 --> 50:46.977
(Erica sighs)

50:53.251 --> 50:55.820
- Captain, you know we can
cut off their GPS signal.

50:58.489 --> 50:59.990
- Why would we wanna do that?

50:59.990 --> 51:01.992
- I'm just saying, we don't
have to follow through.

51:02.026 --> 51:03.994
I'm sure we can think
of something else.

51:03.994 --> 51:05.363
Lieutenant Kruger's
one of the good ones.

51:05.396 --> 51:06.231
What about her?

51:07.398 --> 51:09.567
- Did you leave your
balls in Cape Town?

51:10.868 --> 51:13.371
How many people have
suffered under Frank?

51:13.371 --> 51:16.507
How many more will get
trampled underneath his feet?

51:16.507 --> 51:19.877
If we don't stop him now, their
blood will be on our hands.

51:19.910 --> 51:21.779
I'd rather dip my
toes in a bit of blood

51:21.779 --> 51:23.848
than drown in a swimming
pool full of it.

51:26.384 --> 51:27.252
- Yeah, think bigger.

51:27.252 --> 51:28.686
- Yes!

51:28.719 --> 51:30.221
The bigger picture.

51:30.221 --> 51:35.059
Besides, I think Kruger
can take care of herself.

51:35.926 --> 51:36.727
She's used to hard-asses.

51:42.267 --> 51:45.136
(woman vocalizing)

51:57.615 --> 51:58.449
- Can I help you?

52:16.066 --> 52:17.134
Oh, this is neat.

52:24.675 --> 52:25.610
(drapes swish)

52:25.643 --> 52:26.744
- [Erica] Keep that closed.

52:28.813 --> 52:29.847
(lock clacking)

52:29.914 --> 52:32.583
(keys jingling)

52:43.027 --> 52:44.529
- So which side do I sleep on?

52:45.996 --> 52:46.964
- [Erica] This one.

